## Electrical safety matters in every Srinagar home

Kashmir's climate — cold winters, humid summers, and occasional heavy rainfall — puts extra strain on home electrical systems. Moisture can affect outdoor connections, older wiring may not handle modern appliance loads, and overloaded circuits are a common cause of tripped breakers. Attempting DIY fixes on live circuits is dangerous and can cause further damage.

When you book through Panun Kaergar, you are hiring a professional who understands residential electrical work. Partners on our platform handle jobs with proper tools and safety practices. You can describe the issue in the app — a sparking socket, a fan that hums but does not spin, lights that dim when the geyser turns on — and the assigned electrician arrives prepared for the visit.

For families with children or elderly members at home, knowing that electrical work is done correctly brings real peace of mind. Panun Kaergar's review system also helps the community identify partners who consistently deliver quality work across Srinagar.

