## Tips before your electrician visit in Srinagar

A little preparation helps your booking go smoothly and saves time on site:

- **Switch off affected circuits** if safe to do so, especially if you noticed sparking or burning smells.
- **Clear access** to the switchboard, fuse box, or the room where work is needed.
- **List all issues** in one booking if they are in the same visit — for example, a broken socket and a ceiling fan that needs installation.
- **Note your inverter model** if the job involves backup power, so the partner can bring the right connectors or parts.
- **Be home or have someone available** to show the electrician the problem areas and approve the work.

If the job requires materials — a new MCB, switches, or wiring — your partner can advise on what is needed. Some electricians carry common parts; for specialised items, they may recommend you purchase them locally or return for a follow-up visit.

